column2: Clear sky- very light winds- and surface almost glassy.
Water temperature 48 degrees F from surface to 45 ft- 38 degrees F at 50'.
Ice out 4/21/92.  Water level up- but no noticeable flow of water in channel from Leader to Bond Lake.
Surface water temperature still 4 degrees cooler than one month ago- but 5 degrees warmer than two weeks ago.
Lake near turnover.  Water temperature 57 degrees from surface to 35'- 44 degrees at 40'- 38 degrees at 45'- and 36 degrees at 50' to bottom (62').
Water temperature 38 degrees from surface to the bottom.
Ice out 4/20.  Water temperature at surface on north shoreline in 42 degrees- and in the middle of lake 39 degrees.
Surface water temperature (middle of lake) is 55 degrees- 16 degree increase in 14 days.
Surface water temperature 3 degrees less than reading on May 14.
Water temperature 45 degrees from surface to 55' and 42 at the bottom (61').
Cool and cloudy.  Water temperature is 70 degrees F at the surface.
Ice out April 17- weather is cloudy and cool- 44 degrees- and the wind and water are dead calm.
Water temps. surface 5'=58 degrees- 10'-30'=62 degrees- 40'=48 degrees- 50'=45 degrees- 60'=44 degrees.
Water temps. 1'-58 degrees- 5'-20'=57 degrees- 25'-40'=56 degrees' 50'=49 degrees- 60'=47 degrees.
Sunny- light winds- and 52 degrees- fair temperature.
Sunny- 60 degrees- breezy from the south- perfect fall day.
Ice off April 19.  Very dry and windy.
Very cool weather- water temperature has risen only 2 degrees in 16 days.
May fly hatch about 10 days late.  Water temperature is still very cool or Van Dorn thermometer is not giving accurate readings.
Ice out on April 6- very windy last few days- lake churned up.
Ice out on March 23- earliest that I have ever recorded.
The lake is dead calm.  This is a new record for water clarity.
Windy and a lot of pollen
